article.headline: Arkansas 89, Austin Peay 80
article.story: FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. -- Michael Washington scored 24 points and snared 14 rebounds before fouling out Wednesday night as Arkansas beat Austin Peay 89-80. Four players scored in double figures for Arkansas (7-1). Washington fouled out with a little more than two minutes left. Down the stretch, the Razorbacks were near-perfect from the free throw line to seal Arkansas' 39th straight home nonconference victory. It was the Razorbacks' fifth straight win this season. Freshman point guard Courtney Fortson added 20 points for Arkansas and Rotnei Clarke scored 14, including a clutch 3-pointer with 2 minutes left after Washington fouled out. Stefan Walsh scored 12 points for Arkansas. Clarke's 3-pointer gave Arkansas an 80-73 lead and the Razorbacks made 9-of-10 free throws in the game's closing minutes. Drake Reed led Austin Peay (5-4) with 24 points and Wes Channels added 17.
